{{Infobox person | name = Owen Reed Lovejoy | image =File:Owen Reed Lovejoy in 1917.jpg | caption = Lovejoy in 1917 | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date|1866|9|9}} | birth_place =[[Jamestown, Michigan]] | death_date = {{Death date and age|1961|6|29|1866|9|9}} | death_place =[[Biglerville, Pennsylvania]] | death_cause = | other_names = | known_for = | education =[[Albion College]] | occupation =Minister | spouse =Jennie Evelyn Campbell | partner = | children = | parents =Hiram Reed Lovejoy, Sr.<br>Harriett Helen Robinson | relatives = }}
'''Owen Reed Lovejoy, Jr.''' (September 9, 1866 - June 29, 1961) was a minister who opposed [[child labor]].<ref name=bio/><ref name=obit/> He was known as the "children's statesman".<ref name=bio/> He served as the [[general secretary]] of the [[National Child Labor Committee]] from 1907 to 1926.<ref>{{cite book |author= |title=A year's work of the National Child Labor Committee |year=1920 |publisher=[[National Child Labor Committee]] |page= |quote= | url=http://pds.lib.harvard.edu/pds/view/3654131?n=3&printThumbnails=no |isbn= }}</ref>

==Biography==
He was born on September 9, 1866 in [[Jamestown, Michigan]] to Hiram Reed Lovejoy, Sr. and Harriett Helen Robinson. He attended [[Albion College]]. On June 30, 1892 he married Jennie Evelyn Campbell and they had five children, but only two of his sons survived to adulthood. In 1904 he joined the [[National Child Labor Committee]] and served until 1926. He then went to work for the [[Children's Aid Society]]. His wife died in 1929. In 1937 he married Kate Calkins Drake. He retired in 1939 and moved to [[Biglerville, Pennsylvania]].<ref name=bio/>

He died on June 29, 1961 in [[Biglerville, Pennsylvania]].<ref name=bio>{{cite encyclopedia |author= |encyclopedia =Michigan Biographical Dictionary |title= Owen Reed Lovejoy |year=2008  |publisher= |page=86 |quote= | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=aWR5HJJktL8C&pg=RA1-PA86 |isbn= }}</ref><ref name=obit>{{cite news |author= |agency= |title=Owen R. Lovejoy, Crusader, 94, Dies. Former Minister Was Long a Foe of Child Labor |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1961/06/30/archives/owen-r-lovejoy-crusader-94-dies-former-minister-was-long-a-foe-of.html |quote= |newspaper=[[New York Times]] |date=June 30, 1961 |accessdate=2015-04-24 }}</ref>

