{{Infobox officeholder |honorific-prefix = [[The Honourable]] |name = Wayne Caines |honorific-suffix = [[House of Assembly of Bermuda|MP]] |image = |office1 = Minister of National Security |term_start1 = July 2017 |term_end1 = |monarch1 = |2blankname1 = {{nowrap|Premier}} |2namedata1 = [[Edward David Burt]] |deputy1 = |predecessor1 = |birth_date = |birth_place = |spouse = |children = |alma_mater = |party = [[Progressive Labour Party (Bermuda)|Progressive Labour Party]] }}
'''Wayne Caines''' is a Bermudian politician currently serving as the Minister of National Security since the [[Bermudian general election, 2017|2017 election]]. Caines represents Devonshire North West for the [[Progressive Labour Party (Bermuda)|Progressive Labour Party]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://parliament.bm/cabinet/view/46|title=Bermuda Parliament|website=parliament.bm|accessdate=7 September 2018}}</ref>
==Education and career== Caines is a graduate of [[Oakwood University]] in [[Huntsville, Alabama]], the [[University of Kent]] and the [[Royal Military Academy Sandhurst]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.plp.bm/wayne_caines|title=MP Constituency #14 - Devonshire North West|publisher=|accessdate=7 September 2018}}</ref>
Prior to entering politics, Caines served as a Captain within the [[Bermuda Regiment]] and as a Crown Counsel at the Department of Public Prosecutions.
==Political career== Prior to entering Parliament, Caines was Chief of Staff in the Office of the Premier. He then served as a Progressive Labour Party Senator, becoming Junior Minister of Tourism, Transport, Environment and Sport.
Following the Progressive Labour Party victory at the 2017 election, in which Caines was re-elected as member for Devonshire North West, Caines was appointed as Minister of National Security.
In 2018, Caines attracted media attention in both Bermuda and Britain, after he filmed himself asking female staff at the [[Cereal Killer Cafe]] in London whether "titty milk" was available, which he then posted to [[Instagram]]. After public criticism, Caines issued an apology, telling ''[[The Royal Gazette (Bermuda)|The Royal Gazette]]'' that he was "deeply disappointed" in himself.<ref>{{cite news |last=Johnston-Barnes |first=Owain |date=7 September 2018 |title=Caines called on the carpet |url=http://www.royalgazette.com/politics/article/20180907/caines-called-on-carpet |work=[[The Royal Gazette (Bermuda)|The Royal Gazette]] |location=[[Hamilton, Bermuda|Hamilton]] |access-date=7 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Jarvis|first=Jacob |date=7 September 2018 |title=Senior politician from Bermuda apologises after asking female staff at London's Cereal Killer Café if they have 't***y milk' |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/news/london/bermudan-politician-apologises-after-asking-female-staff-at-londons-cereal-killer-cafe-if-they-have-a3930161.html |work=[[London Evening Standard]] |location=[[London]] |access-date=7 September 2018}}</ref>
